00:38:16,208 --> 00:38:17,291
Please confirm.

774
00:38:17,291 --> 00:38:18,792
Analysis confirmed.

775
00:38:18,792 --> 00:38:20,333
Probable cause?

776
00:38:20,333 --> 00:38:22,375
Replication.

777
00:38:22,375 --> 00:38:23,917
Compare these variations

778
00:38:23,917 --> 00:38:26,792
with established Romulan
replication patterns.

779
00:38:26,792 --> 00:38:28,417
The patterns are identical.

780
00:38:31,959 --> 00:38:33,417
Then maybe we should run
a level-1 diagnostic

781
00:38:33,417 --> 00:38:35,041
on those phase
transition coils.

782
00:38:35,041 --> 00:38:36,291
Right, Commander.

783
00:38:43,250 --> 00:38:44,709
PICARD:
I'm still confident...

784
00:38:47,750 --> 00:38:50,458
Data to La Forge.

785
00:38:50,458 --> 00:38:52,125
Report, please.

786
00:38:52,125 --> 00:38:53,375
Geordi.

787
00:38:53,375 --> 00:38:54,625
Please respond.

788
00:38:58,542 --> 00:39:01,959
Computer, current location
of Commander La Forge.

789
00:39:01,959 --> 00:39:04,250
Cargo Bay Four.

790
00:39:04,250 --> 00:39:05,417
Data to Lieutenant Worf.

791
00:39:05,417 --> 00:39:07,959
Priority One.

792
00:39:07,959 --> 00:39:09,667
Go ahead.

793
00:39:09,667 --> 00:39:13,500
Take Commander La Forge
into custody immediately.

794
00:39:13,500 --> 00:39:14,583
Sir?

795
00:39:14,583 --> 00:39:16,500
That is an order.

796
00:39:16,500 --> 00:39:18,041
PICARD:
We've been looking
for DNA samples.

797
00:39:18,041 --> 00:39:20,500
By tracing
the biochemical signatures

798
00:39:20,500 --> 00:39:21,750
they will be able
to determine

799
00:39:21,750 --> 00:39:23,375
who was in this bay
recently.

800
00:39:23,375 --> 00:39:26,041
VAGH:
But how will it be possible
to prove which one...

801
00:39:30,333 --> 00:39:31,709
<i>Q'ac Ken ta'vak!</i>

802
00:39:33,417 --> 00:39:34,834
La Forge!

803
00:39:44,208 --> 00:39:45,875
Mr. Worf, get
him out of here.

804
00:39:53,583 --> 00:39:56,125
Arming our enemies
is not enough.

805
00:39:56,125 --> 00:40:00,750
Now the Federation would
murder me to achieve its aims.

806
00:40:00,750 --> 00:40:04,583
Governor, if I could
explain this, I would.

807
00:40:04,583 --> 00:40:07,083
I believe I can help,
Captain.

808
00:40:07,083 --> 00:40:09,166
I've been able to determine
that Commander La Forge

809
00:40:09,166 --> 00:40:12,458
was abducted by Romulans
en route to Risa.

810
00:40:12,458 --> 00:40:13,542
It is likely that he was

811
00:40:13,542 --> 00:40:14,917
somehow forced
to take part

812
00:40:14,917 --> 00:40:17,083
in the plot
to assassinate
Governor Vagh.

813
00:40:17,083 --> 00:40:19,125
I saw no evidence
of Romulans.

814
00:40:19,125 --> 00:40:21,500
We just witnessed him
acting very much alone.

815
00:40:21,500 --> 00:40:24,166
No, sir, you did not.

816
00:40:24,166 --> 00:40:25,291
I do not believe
the Commander

817
00:40:25,291 --> 00:40:27,250
is acting
of his own accord.

818
00:40:27,250 --> 00:40:28,375
He has been receiving

819
00:40:28,375 --> 00:40:30,667
E-band signals
through his VISOR--

820
00:40:30,667 --> 00:40:31,834
signals which
are carrying

821
00:40:31,834 --> 00:40:33,792
direct commands
to his brain.

822
00:40:33,792 --> 00:40:36,375
I have surmised
that Commander La Forge

823
00:40:36,375 --> 00:40:38,458
was conditioned by Romulans

824
00:40:38,458 --> 00:40:40,583
a process
referred to
historically--

825
00:40:40,583 --> 00:40:43,625
and somewhat inaccurately--
as "brainwashing."

826
00:40:43,625 --> 00:40:45,333
VAGH:
But to what end?

827
00:40:45,333 --> 00:40:47,625
Why would the Romulans
want to kill me?

828
00:40:47,625 --> 00:40:49,709
The Romulans have always wanted
to destroy the alliance

829
00:40:49,709 --> 00:40:52,041
between the Federation
and the Klingons.

830
00:40:52,041 --> 00:40:54,208
If Mr. La Forge
had killed you, Governor

831
00:40:54,208 --> 00:40:55,375
I think
you would agree

832
00:40:55,375 --> 00:40:56,709
they might have
succeeded.

833
00:40:56,709 --> 00:40:58,458
Who sent these signals?

834
00:40:58,458 --> 00:41:00,333
A cloaked Romulan ship?

835
00:41:00,333 --> 00:41:01,500
DATA:
No, sir.

836
00:41:01,500 --> 00:41:02,583
That is not possible.

837
00:41:02,583 --> 00:41:03,917
The signals had
to be transmitted

838
00:41:03,917 --> 00:41:07,333
within close proximity
to the VISOR.

839
00:41:07,333 --> 00:41:08,625
Are you suggesting
that there was

840
00:41:08,625 --> 00:41:10,250
a Romulan accomplice
in close proximity

841
00:41:10,250 --> 00:41:12,834
to Mr. La Forge when he
was receiving the signals?

842
00:41:12,834 --> 00:41:14,166
Yes, sir, I am.

843
00:41:14,166 --> 00:41:16,709
VAGH:
This Romulan
accomplice

844
00:41:16,709 --> 00:41:18,208
who is he?

845
00:41:18,208 --> 00:41:19,375
I have narrowed the list

846
00:41:19,375 --> 00:41:21,333
of possibilities
to two people--

847
00:41:21,333 --> 00:41:22,458
the only two people

848
00:41:22,458 --> 00:41:23,875
who were with
Commander La Forge

849
00:41:23,875 --> 00:41:27,125
all three times
a transmission
was recorded--

850
00:41:27,125 --> 00:41:30,917
Captain Picard
and Ambassador Kell.

851
00:41:30,917 --> 00:41:32,583
One of them
may be concealing

852
00:41:32,583 --> 00:41:34,834
an E-band transmitter.

853
00:41:34,834 --> 00:41:36,375
If they would agree
to be searched...

854
00:41:36,375 --> 00:41:39,834
I am a Klingon,
an emissary of the High Council.

855
00:41:39,834 --> 00:41:41,875
I will not submit
to being searched

856
00:41:41,875 --> 00:41:43,500
by you or anyone else
on this ship.

857
00:41:43,500 --> 00:41:46,041
VAGH:
I am forced to
agree, Captain.

858
00:41:46,041 --> 00:41:47,959
We will take the Ambassador
with us

859
00:41:47,959 --> 00:41:51,709
and search him ourselves.

860
00:41:51,709 --> 00:41:54,875
Captain, I believe it to be
in all our best interests

861
00:41:54,875 --> 00:41:56,583
if I remain aboard.

862
00:41:56,583 --> 00:41:59,959
I formally request asylum.

863
00:41:59,959 --> 00:42:02,917
I will certainly
grant you asylum...

864
00:42:02,917 --> 00:42:06,792
when you have been absolved
of this crime.

865
00:42:06,792 --> 00:42:08,458
<i>Gurt'ank te'la.</i>

866
00:42:20,917 --> 00:42:23,542
But I<i> remember</i> everything!

867
00:42:25,250 --> 00:42:27,166
Like, there was this one night
at dinner.

868
00:42:27,166 --> 00:42:28,709
We had this Andorian waiter.

869
00:42:28,709 --> 00:42:30,250
He couldn't get
our orders right.

870
00:42:32,417 --> 00:42:34,500
It<i> did</i> happen!

871
00:42:34,500 --> 00:42:37,166
I remember
being on Risa.

872
00:42:37,166 --> 00:42:39,750
I know you do.

873
00:42:39,750 --> 00:42:43,917
Just take that memory
and put it aside for a moment

874
00:42:43,917 --> 00:42:46,417
and tell me
everything you remember

875
00:42:46,417 --> 00:42:50,375
about the shuttlecraft trip
after you left the<i> Enterprise.</i>

876
00:42:50,375 --> 00:42:52,000
(<i> sighs</i> )

877
00:42:55,000 --> 00:42:57,500
Well, I... I was just trying
to get in the mood.

878
00:42:57,500 --> 00:43:00,458
I, uh...

879
00:43:00,458 --> 00:43:01,917
I played some music.

880
00:43:01,917 --> 00:43:03,583
I talked to the computer.

881
00:43:03,583 --> 00:43:05,583
You know what it's like
on a long trip.

882
00:43:05,583 --> 00:43:07,166
And when you saw
the Romulan ship

883
00:43:07,166 --> 00:43:08,875
did you try and call for help?

884
00:43:08,875 --> 00:43:10,166
No, the first thing I did...

885
00:43:15,125 --> 00:43:16,875
Wait a minute.
That...

886
00:43:19,375 --> 00:43:21,542
But that's...

887
00:43:21,542 --> 00:43:23,834
It'll take time, Geordi.

888
00:43:23,834 --> 00:43:26,333
A long time.

889
00:43:26,333 --> 00:43:29,208
But we will reconstruct
your memory...

890
00:43:29,208 --> 00:43:30,750
together.

891
00:43:40,834 --> 00:43:43,291
I'm just not sure...

892
00:43:47,542 --> 00:43:50,750
about anything.

893
00:43:50,750 --> 00:43:54,417
Believe it or not,
that's a good sign.

894
00:43:54,417 --> 00:43:56,291
A beginning.

895
00:43:57,500 --> 00:44:02,083
Now, let's go back
to the shuttlecraft.

896
00:44:02,083 --> 00:44:03,625
There was a Romulan ship

897
00:44:03,625 --> 00:44:05,625
and the first thing
you did was...?
